  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Take your<strong> chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air, then pat the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> dry with kitchen paper and season them with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>berbere seasoning </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick and with a matching lid) over a medium-high heat and once hot, add the<strong> seasoned chicken</strong>, skin-side down and cook for 7-8 min or until the skins have browned and crisped</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1687337699056-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1687337699056-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1687337699056-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1687337699056-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1687337699056-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice <strong>half </strong>the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Slice the <strong>remaining onion</strong> finely</p><p>Chop the <strong>tomatoes</strong> finely</p><p>Drain and rinse the <strong>green lentils</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1687337703180-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1687337703180-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1687337703180-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1687337703180-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1687337703180-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken skin has crisped, transfer the <strong>browned</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined tray and reserve the pan</p><p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 25-30 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your<strong> crispy berbere chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1687337709261-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1687337709261-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1687337709261-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1687337709261-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1687337709261-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p><p>Rip the leaves off the <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p><p>Wash the <strong>sliced spring greens</strong> then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1687337713368-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1687337713368-x400.jpg",
